subSubSection.paragraph:
Uropod
(
Fig. 2G
) [of 
holotype
] over half length of pleotelson; peduncle longer than broad, naked; endopod 1.3 times longer than peduncle, weakly two-segmented, segment-1 larger than segment-2, with one distal simple seta and two distomesial PSS, segment-2 with one short and three long setae, and one PSS; exopod one-segmented, caplike, articulation with peduncle indistinct, with two distal setae.
